r, Wyoming. The work, by artist Chris Navarro, is a tongue-in-cheek reference to Wyoming cowboys' lot in winter: unpredictable, sideways blizzards in which they have to work, saving livestock, sometimes including newborn calves and lambs who would starve and freeze to death in the bitter cold", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2017688157/"}], "resource": {"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/wyu/batch_wyu_frannie_ver01/data/sn86072160/00514150345/1920092501/0657.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:wyu:batch_wyu_frannie_ver01:data:sn86072160:00514150345:1920092501:0657/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/wyu/batch_wyu_frannie_ver01/data/sn86072160/00514150345/1920092501/0657.pdf", "segment_count": 12, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86072160/1920-09-25/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}, "resources": [{"fulltext_file": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/wyu/batch_wyu_frannie_ver01/data/sn86072160/00514150345/1920092501/0657.xml&format=alto_xml&full_text=1", "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:wyu:batch_wyu_frannie_ver01:data:sn86072160:00514150345:1920092501:0657/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/ndnp/wyu/batch_wyu_frannie_ver01/data/sn86072160/00514150345/1920092501/0657.pdf", "segment_count": 12, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86072160/1920-09-25/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/wyu/batch_wyu_frannie_ver01/data/sn86072160/00514150345/1920092501/0657.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86072160/1920-09-25/ed-1/?sp=1"], "batch": ["wyu_frannie_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/wyoming/", "2/united states/wyoming/natrona/", "3/united states/wyoming/natrona/casper/"], "contributor": ["university of wyoming libraries"], "date": "1920-09-25", "dates": ["1920-09-25"], "description": ["INDICTMENTS PROBABLE IN WHITE SC SCATL lv Cciiiprr tkulif WEATHER FORECAST ts c a Fair tonight and Sunday tome g W S3MS I SS what warmer m central portion H Rd j ijP tonight W V W W K c N W Arrive Leave No 606 Eastbound _235 pan Ztt pan 2 No 603 Westbound__32o pan 340 pan VOLUME IV Douglas Light Plant Is Fired Up After Receiver Is Appointed by Court Normal Conditions Restored After City Goes Without Light or Power for Two Days Rate Increase Turned Down by State Commission May Be Granted Now Special to The Tribune DOUGLAS Wyo Sept 25The Douglas Electric Light Com pany fired np under its boilers again this morning after the city had been without light and power since 6 oclock Thursday evening when the company carried out its decision to discontinue servce of all kinds and cease operation Normal conditions will be restored in a few hours it is believed although it will take longer to recover from the inconvenience caused during the past two days particularly among those who depended upon the electric com pany for power Resumption of operations was made possible through an application for a receivership granted"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2023-05-31T13:49:13.979Z", "group": ["ndnp/wyu", "university-of-wyoming-libraries"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn86072160/1920-09-25/ed-1/?sp=1", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:wyu:batch_wyu_frannie_ver01:data:sn86072160:00514150345:1920092501:0657/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=295&w=235", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:wyu:batch_wyu_frannie_ver01:data:sn86072160:00514150345:1920092501:0657/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=590&w=471", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-